                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d750">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Legation of the United States</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-02-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 17, 1895</hi>
                        </date>. (Received March 8.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 433.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have secured through an unofficial request the
                    recognition by iradé of the acquired nationality of Socrates Seferiades, about
                    whom there was so much trouble. He is a native Greek and a gentleman. He failed
                    to inform me of facts regarding his business connection with American
                    industries, which, if known at first, would have caused me to recognize his
                    citizenship. The iradé relieves me, and will exempt him from molestation.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
